	   <a name=103864684734055></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103864684734055><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: Besides the fact.....</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=182685><span id=Sage>Tluadanmudvayne</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>81 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Nov 30th 4:23 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I Personally Would like to know what kind of char you play that makes you think that Druids are Overpowered and Unbalanced. They are Powered and Balanced Perfectly. Druids, if you look at their abality's, they are Half Wizard, half Cleric, But dont have the Power of either one of them. Cleric's, at lvl 60, get Ageo, which gives 1100 HP's to a Person, Druids Get Protection of the glades which give's approx 500 to 600 HP's to a person. At lvl 43, My Nuke Spell Hits for 300 (298 to be exact) Max. I play EQ with a Wizard that's in her 30's that has a nuke that hits harder than that. Also, Druids Have a low AC and HP amounts. Cleric's can have Good AC because they can Wear Plated Armor, and wizard's have bad AC cause they only wear Robes. Druids Can Wear Leather, so they have a Mid grade AC. <br>Also, my Druid at 43, has a whole 800-850hp's, so Getting Killed by something is pretty easy. So once again, a Druid is Stuck in the Middle, with &quot;Not as good as one, but a little better than the other&quot;. <br>Druids are perfectly Balanced. They have the Advantage of Being able to Do Most of the things a Wizard can, and Most of the things that clerics Can, But Is no where as good at healing, as a cleric is, or at nukeing, as a wizard is. Also, the next time you are about to ask a Druid for buff's, tell them their Unbalanced and Over powered before you do, and see if you dont get told to go to a Cleric insted then, Since Druids are So Overpowered for buff's. Do the same if you pull a Druid into your group to nuke, and see if you dont get told to get a Wizard then. <br><br>P.S.--Point Made, and not ment to Bash you. Its your Opinion, and So be it. Good Day!<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Tluadan Mudvayne<br>55th Season Preserver<br>&lt;Arctic Flame&gt;<br>-----------------------<br>Freight Turazz<br>35th Ring Paladin<br>&lt;Arctic Flame&gt;</td></tr>
